{
  "texts": [
    "For example, research by Haripriya et al. (2023) demonstrated that machine learning could classify breath samples to detect early-stage lung cancer based on specific VOC profiles.",
    "This innovative, non-invasive screening method offers a cost-effective alternative to traditional diagnostic techniques, facilitating early intervention that can lead to improved patient outcomes.",
    "Furthermore, AI-enhanced olfactory systems are deployed to detect hazardous gases, pollutants, and industrial leaks in environmental monitoring.",
    "By utilizing algorithms like LSTMs and transformers, these systems analyze time-series data from sensor arrays to ensure real-time air quality monitoring, allowing for rapid responses to environmental hazards (Dalal et al. 2024).",
    "Similarly, the food and beverage industry benefits from AI-powered systems for quality control, employing pattern recognition techniques to identify spoilage and contamination (Zatsu et al. 2024)."
  ]
}